## Scenario 2 — Chemical Spill in Secondary Containment (No Breach)
##
## Containment is the primary gate, NOT quantity. Per EPA/DOE guidance
## DOE/EH-0447 (1995), a release into intact secondary containment is
## not a release "to the environment" under CERCLA §101(22). No
## CERCLA 103 / EPCRA 304 reporting fires. No transport context → no
## DOT. Becomes a waste-disposal event: EPA RCRA + OSHA HCS.
##
## Routing narrows relative to Scenario 1 because the containment
## condition is present. This ASK verifies the narrowed routing.
##
## Baseline triples extracted from ehs-ontology-v3.2.ttl (line 1206).

PREFIX ehs: <http://example.org/ehs-ontology#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

ASK {
    ehs:Scenario_ChemSpill_Contained rdf:type ehs:ContextualComplianceActivation ;
        ehs:triggeredByType       ehs:ChemicalHazard ;
        ehs:hasActionContext      ehs:WasteHandlingAction ;
        ehs:hasContextCondition   ehs:SecondaryContainmentArea ,
                                  ehs:FullyContained ;
        ehs:activatesFramework    ehs:EPA_Framework ,
                                  ehs:OSHA_Framework .
}
